In his remarks at a luncheon hosted by Secretary General Ban Ki-Moon at the United Nations Headquarters, President Obama welcomed the attendees and thanked them for their work. He praised the Secretary General for his outstanding work in mobilizing the world around urgent challenges such as humanitarian disasters, sustainable development goals, and climate change. President Obama emphasized the importance of the United Nations in resolving conflicts, protecting vulnerable people, and strengthening international cooperation. He acknowledged the extraordinary challenges faced today, including humanitarian crises, threats to the international order, and human rights issues. Despite these challenges, President Obama expressed optimism in tackling them if everyone works together, with the United Nations playing a critical role. He highlighted the importance of boldness, imagination, political will, and recognizing our common humanity in solving the problems caused by mankind. President Obama concluded by proposing a toast to all nations, the United Nations, and the pursuit of progress and peace.